    "biography": "<p>Looking much like a horse-sized hairless lion with mottled hide, a courser is a vicious pack hunter often &ldquo;domesticated&rdquo; as a mount for elite Anak warriors. While they can survive on plant matter, coursers much prefer meat. Even when ridden, a courser can fight independently and can leap up to 30&rsquo; as a Main Action, giving the crusaders of Sarul their famous tactic of leaping over an enemy force&rsquo;s front lines to savage the spear wall from the rear.</p>"
